**Key Points:**
- A period usually happens once a month
- It typically lasts 3-7 days
- Most girls get their first period between ages 10-15
- Periods are a normal part of growing up

**What to Expect:**
- You may see red or brown blood
- You might feel cramps in your lower belly
- You can use pads, tampons, or menstrual cups
- It's normal for periods to be irregular at first

