**The Four Phases:**

1. **Menstruation (Days 1-5)**
   - The lining of the uterus sheds
   - This is when you have your period
   - Bleeding typically lasts 3-7 days

2. **Follicular Phase (Days 1-13)**
   - Your body prepares to release an egg
   - Hormone levels increase
   - You may feel more energetic

3. **Ovulation (Day 14)**
   - An egg is released from the ovary
   - This is when you're most fertile
   - Some people feel mild pain called mittelschmerz

4. **Luteal Phase (Days 15-28)**
   - The body prepares for possible pregnancy
   - If pregnancy doesn't occur, the cycle restarts
   - PMS symptoms may occur during this time

**Tracking Your Cycle:**
- Use a calendar, app, or journal
- Note when your period starts and ends
- Track any symptoms or mood changes
- This helps you understand what's normal for you`,
